\section2 ComboBox

A button with a dropdown that allows selecting one of several options.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} ComboBox

\row
    \li{1, 6} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} Hovered
\row
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} VisualFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Pressed
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled
\row
    \li{2, 1} Highlighted

\row
    \li{1, 3} \b{Hints}
    \li \b flat
    \li Set whenever the combobox should use a flat appearance.
\row
    \li \b editable
    \li Set whenever the combobox is user-editable and should display that.
\row
    \li \b changed
    \li Set whenever the combobox should visualize a changed state.


\endtable

\section3 Sub-Elements

\section4 Icon

The icon displayed by the button. Style it using the icon related
properties.




\section4 Text

The text displayed by the button. Style it using the text related
properties.




\section4 Indicator

An icon used to indicate that this is a combobox. Should use a down
arrow icon or similar.


\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} Indicator




\endtable


\section4 Popup

The dropdown displayed by the combobox.

\note This subelement is not a descendant of the combobox, so you
cannot target it with child or descrendant selectors. Instead, use
the type and "combobox" hint to target the popup.


\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} Popup


\row
    \li{1, 1} \b{Hints}
    \li \b combobox
    \li Used to indicate that this is a combobox popup.


\endtable


\section4 Delegate

The combobox has a delegate that is used by the dropdown. By default
this delegate will be an ItemDelegate but it may be overridden by
applications.






